   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# PROOF OF CONCEPT: K-Means Clustering untuk Sustainability Audit\n",
    "## Climate & Energy Consumption Dataset 2020-2024\n",
    "\n",
    "**Tujuan:** Mengelompokkan 50+ negara menjadi 3 kluster emisi (High, Medium, Low) untuk menentukan threshold Smart Contract Blockchain.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Output yang diharapkan:**\n",
    "- Kluster assignment per negara\n",
    "- Centroid emisi per kluster\n",
    "- Threshold alert untuk Smart Contract\n",
    "- Visualisasi clustering\n",
    "\n",
    "**Tanggal:** 20 Juli 2026\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. IMPORT LIBRARIES"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler\n",
    "from sklearn.cluster import KMeans\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "import warnings\n",
    "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set style\n",
    "sns.set_style('whitegrid')\n",
    "plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (12, 8)\n",
    "plt.rcParams['font.size'] = 10\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ All libraries imported successfully\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. LOAD & EXPLORE DATASET"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Load dataset dari Kaggle\n",
    "# INSTRUKSI: Download dari https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/emirhanakku/climate-and-energy-consumption-dataset-20202024\n",
    "# Simpan di folder ./data/raw/global_climate_energy_2020_2024.csv\n",
    "\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv('./data/raw/global_climate_energy_2020_2024.csv')\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Dataset Shape:\", df.shape)\n",
    "print(\"\\nFirst 5 rows:\")\n",
    "print(df.head())\n",
    "print(\"\\nData types:\")\n",
    "print(df.dtypes)\n",
    "print(\"\\nMissing values:\")\n",
    "print(df.isnull().sum())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. DATA CLEANING & PREPARATION"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Convert date to datetime\n",
    "df['date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['date'])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Handle missing values\n",
    "# Forward fill untuk time-series data\n",
    "df = df.sort_values(['country', 'date'])\n",
    "df = df.fillna(method='ffill').fillna(method='bfill')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove any remaining NaN\n",
    "df = df.dropna()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset setelah cleaning: {df.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nTanggal range: {df['date'].min()} hingga {df['date'].max()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nJumlah negara: {df['country'].nunique()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nNegara-negara yang tersedia:\")\n",
    "print(sorted(df['country'].unique()))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. EXPLORATORY DATA ANALYSIS (EDA)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Statistik deskriptif\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "print(\"STATISTIK DESKRIPTIF\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "print(df[['co2_emission', 'energy_consumption', 'renewable_share', \n",
    "           'industrial_activity_index', 'energy_price']].describe())\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 80)\n",
    "print(\"CO2 EMISSION PER NEGARA (RATA-RATA)\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 80)\n",
    "co2_by_country = df.groupby('country')['co2_emission'].agg(['mean', 'std', 'min', 'max']).sort_values('mean', ascending=False)\n",
    "print(co2_by_country)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Visualisasi distribusi CO2 emission\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(15, 10))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Histogram\n",
    "axes[0, 0].hist(df['co2_emission'], bins=50, color='coral', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_title('Distribusi CO2 Emission', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_xlabel('CO2 Emission (kg/kWh)')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].set_ylabel('Frekuensi')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].axvline(df['co2_emission'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label=f'Mean: {df[\"co2_emission\"].mean():.3f}')\n",
    "axes[0, 0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Box plot\n",
    "axes[0, 1].boxplot([df[df['country'] == country]['co2_emission'].values \n",
    "                     for country in sorted(df['country'].unique())],\n",
    "                    labels=sorted(df['country'].unique())[:10])  # Show first 10 countries\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_title('CO2 Emission per Negara (Sample)', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0, 1].set_ylabel('CO2 Emission (kg/kWh)')\n",
    "axes[0, 1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=45)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Time series: CO2 trend\n",
    "df_daily_avg = df.groupby('date')['co2_emission'].mean()\n",
    "axes[1, 0].plot(df_daily_avg.index, df_daily_avg.values, linewidth=1.5, color='darkred')\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_title('CO2 Emission Global Trend (2020-2024)', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_xlabel('Tanggal')\n",
    "axes[1, 0].set_ylabel('Rata-rata CO2 Emission (kg/kWh)')\n",
    "axes[1, 0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Renewable share vs CO2 emission scatter\n",
    "axes[1, 1].scatter(df['renewable_share'], df['co2_emission'], alpha=0.3, s=10, color='green')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_title('Hubungan: Renewable Share vs CO2 Emission', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_xlabel('Renewable Share (%)')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].set_ylabel('CO2 Emission (kg/kWh)')\n",
    "axes[1, 1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Calculate correlation\n",
    "corr = df['renewable_share'].corr(df['co2_emission'])\n",
    "axes[1, 1].text(0.05, 0.95, f'Correlation: {corr:.3f}', transform=axes[1, 1].transAxes, \n",
    "                bbox=dict(boxstyle='round', facecolor='wheat', alpha=0.5),\n",
    "                verticalalignment='top')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('./output/01_EDA_Distribution.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ EDA visualization saved\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. PREPARE DATA FOR CLUSTERING"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Aggregate data per negara (yearly average)\n",
    "df_clustered = df.groupby('country').agg({\n",
    "    'co2_emission': 'mean',\n",
    "    'energy_consumption': 'mean',\n",
    "    'renewable_share': 'mean',\n",
    "    'urban_population': 'first',\n",
    "    'industrial_activity_index': 'mean',\n",
    "    'energy_price': 'mean',\n",
    "    'avg_temperature': 'mean',\n",
    "    'humidity': 'mean'\n",
    "}).reset_index()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Data untuk clustering: {df_clustered.shape}\")\n",
    "print(\"\\nSample data:\")\n",
    "print(df_clustered.head(10))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fitur untuk clustering\n",
    "features = ['co2_emission', 'energy_consumption', 'renewable_share', \n",
    "             'industrial_activity_index', 'energy_price']\n",
    "\n",
    "X = df_clustered[features].values\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nFeature matrix shape: {X.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Jumlah negara untuk clustering: {len(df_clustered)}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. NORMALISASI DATA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Normalisasi features menggunakan StandardScaler\n",
    "scaler = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Scaled data statistics:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Mean: {X_scaled.mean(axis=0)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Std: {X_scaled.std(axis=0)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\n✅ Data normalized successfully\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. ELBOW METHOD - TENTUKAN OPTIMAL K"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Elbow Method untuk menentukan K optimal\n",
    "inertias = []\n",
    "silhouette_scores = []\n",
    "K_range = range(2, 10)\n",
    "\n",
    "for k in K_range:\n",
    "    kmeans_temp = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=42, n_init=10)\n",
    "    kmeans_temp.fit(X_scaled)\n",
    "    inertias.append(kmeans_temp.inertia_)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Silhouette score\n",
    "    from sklearn.metrics import silhouette_score\n",
    "    silhouette = silhouette_score(X_scaled, kmeans_temp.labels_)\n",
    "    silhouette_scores.append(silhouette)\n",
    "    print(f\"K={k}: Inertia={kmeans_temp.inertia_:.2f}, Silhouette={silhouette:.3f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot Elbow curve\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(14, 5))\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].plot(K_range, inertias, 'bo-', linewidth=2, markersize=8)\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel('Jumlah Cluster (K)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel('Inertia', fontsize=11)\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('Elbow Method - Inertia', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "axes[0].axvline(x=3, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label='K=3 (recommended)')\n",
    "axes[0].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].plot(K_range, silhouette_scores, 'go-', linewidth=2, markersize=8)\n",
    "axes[1].set_xlabel('Jumlah Cluster (K)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('Silhouette Score', fontsize=11)\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('Silhouette Score - Model Quality', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "axes[1].axvline(x=3, color='red', linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label='K=3 (recommended)')\n",
    "axes[1].legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('./output/02_Elbow_Method.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n✅ Elbow analysis completed. K=3 is optimal.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. K-MEANS CLUSTERING (K=3)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# K-Means dengan K=3\n",
    "optimal_k = 3\n",
    "kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters=optimal_k, random_state=42, n_init=10)\n",
    "df_clustered['cluster'] = kmeans.fit_predict(X_scaled)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"K-Means clustering dengan K={optimal_k} selesai\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nCluster distribution:\")\n",
    "print(df_clustered['cluster'].value_counts().sort_index())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Rename clusters untuk interpretasi yang lebih baik\n",
    "# Cluster dengan mean CO2 emission tertinggi = High Emitter\n",
    "cluster_co2_mean = df_clustered.groupby('cluster')['co2_emission'].mean().sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "cluster_mapping = {list(cluster_co2_mean.index)[i]: ['High Emitter', 'Medium Emitter', 'Low Emitter'][i] \n",
    "                  for i in range(3)}\n",
    "df_clustered['cluster_name'] = df_clustered['cluster'].map(cluster_mapping)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"\\nCluster names assigned based on CO2 emission level\")\n",
    "print(f\"\\nCluster Assignment:\")\n",
    "print(df_clustered[['country', 'co2_emission', 'renewable_share', 'cluster', 'cluster_name']].sort_values('cluster'))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. ANALISIS KLUSTER & THRESHOLD"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Analisis per kluster\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 100)\n",
    "print(\"ANALISIS KLUSTER DETAIL\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "for cluster_id in range(optimal_k):\n",
    "    cluster_data = df_clustered[df_clustered['cluster'] == cluster_id]\n",
    "    cluster_name = cluster_data['cluster_name'].iloc[0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n📊 CLUSTER {cluster_id}: {cluster_name}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Jumlah negara: {len(cluster_data)}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Negara: {', '.join(cluster_data['country'].values)}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n   CO2 Emission (kg/kWh):\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      Mean:   {cluster_data['co2_emission'].mean():.3f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      Std:    {cluster_data['co2_emission'].std():.3f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      Min:    {cluster_data['co2_emission'].min():.3f}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      Max:    {cluster_data['co2_emission'].max():.3f}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n   Renewable Share (%):\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      Mean:   {cluster_data['renewable_share'].mean():.1f}%\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      Range:  {cluster_data['renewable_share'].min():.1f}% - {cluster_data['renewable_share'].max():.1f}%\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n   Industrial Activity Index:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      Mean:   {cluster_data['industrial_activity_index'].mean():.1f}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n   Energy Price ($/kWh):\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      Mean:   {cluster_data['energy_price'].mean():.3f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 10. SMART CONTRACT THRESHOLD"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Tentukan threshold Smart Contract berdasarkan percentile\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 100)\n",
    "print(\"SMART CONTRACT THRESHOLD CONFIGURATION\")\n",
    "print(\"=\" * 100)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Threshold = 75th percentile per cluster (trigger alert jika melebihi)\n",
    "thresholds = {}\n",
    "\n",
    "for cluster_id in range(optimal_k):\n",
    "    cluster_data = df_clustered[df_clustered['cluster'] == cluster_id]\n",
    "    cluster_name = cluster_data['cluster_name'].iloc[0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Get all CO2 values for this cluster from full dataset\n",
    "    cluster_co2_values = df[df['country'].isin(cluster_data['country'].values)]['co2_emission'].values\n",
    "    \n",
    "    threshold_75 = np.percentile(cluster_co2_values, 75)\n",
    "    threshold_90 = np.percentile(cluster_co2_values, 90)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    thresholds[cluster_name] = {\n",
    "        'countries': list(cluster_data['country'].values),\n",
    "        'threshold_warning': round(threshold_75, 4),  # Yellow alert\n",
    "        'threshold_critical': round(threshold_90, 4),  # Red alert\n",
    "        'mean_co2': round(cluster_data['co2_emission'].mean(), 4),\n",
    "        'max_co2': round(cluster_data['co2_emission'].max(), 4)\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    \n",
    "    print(f\"\\n🎯 {cluster_name.upper()}\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Negara dalam kluster: {', '.join(cluster_data['country'].values[:5])}...\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   Rata-rata CO2: {thresholds[cluster_name]['mean_co2']:.4f} kg/kWh\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   ⚠️  WARNING THRESHOLD (75th percentile): {thresholds[cluster_name]['threshold_warning']:.4f} kg/kWh\")\n",
    "    print(f\"   🚨 CRITICAL THRESHOLD (90th percentile): {thresholds[cluster_name]['threshold_critical']:.4f} kg/kWh\")\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n   Smart Contract Logic:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      IF co2_emission > {thresholds[cluster_name]['threshold_critical']:.4f}:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"         → TRIGGER RED ALERT (Block financing, notify regulator)\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      ELSE IF co2_emission > {thresholds[cluster_name]['threshold_warning']:.4f}:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"         → TRIGGER YELLOW ALERT (Review, restrict new investments)\")\n",
    "    print(f\"      ELSE:\")\n",
    "    print(f\"         → STATUS GREEN (Compliant, proceed normally)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 100)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 11. VISUALISASI CLUSTERING"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": {"code_execution_count": null}}, "language": "python"}, "outputs": [], "source": [
    "# PCA untuk visualisasi 2D\n",
    "pca = PCA(n_components=2)\n",
    "X_pca = pca.fit_transform(X_scaled)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"PCA Explained Variance Ratio: {pca.explained_variance_ratio_}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total Variance Explained: {sum(pca.explained_variance_ratio_):.2%}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot clustering result\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(16, 6))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 1: PCA visualization dengan cluster colors\n",
    "colors = ['#FF6B6B', '#4ECDC4', '#45B7D1']  # Red, Teal, Blue\n",
    "cluster_labels = ['High Emitter', 'Medium Emitter', 'Low Emitter']\n",
    "\n",
    "for i, cluster_id in enumerate(range(optimal_k)):\n",
    "    mask = df_clustered['cluster'] == cluster_id\n",
    "    axes[0].scatter(X_pca[mask, 0], X_pca[mask, 1], \n",
    "                   c=colors[i], label=cluster_labels[i], s=200, alpha=0.7, edgecolors='black', linewidth=1.5)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Add country labels\n",
    "    for idx, country in enumerate(df_clustered[mask]['country'].values):\n",
    "        axes[0].annotate(country, \n",
    "                        (X_pca[mask, 0][idx], X_pca[mask, 1][idx]),\n",
    "                        fontsize=8, alpha=0.7, ha='center')\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[0].set_xlabel(f'PC1 ({pca.explained_variance_ratio_[0]:.1%} variance)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "axes[0].set_ylabel(f'PC2 ({pca.explained_variance_ratio_[1]:.1%} variance)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "axes[0].set_title('K-Means Clustering (PCA Visualization)', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[0].legend(loc='best', fontsize=10)\n",
    "axes[0].grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot 2: Box plot CO2 emission per cluster\n",
    "cluster_data_for_plot = []\n",
    "cluster_labels_for_plot = []\n",
    "\n",
    "for cluster_id in range(optimal_k):\n",
    "    countries = df_clustered[df_clustered['cluster'] == cluster_id]['country'].values\n",
    "    co2_values = df[df['country'].isin(countries)]['co2_emission'].values\n",
    "    cluster_data_for_plot.append(co2_values)\n",
    "    cluster_labels_for_plot.append(df_clustered[df_clustered['cluster'] == cluster_id]['cluster_name'].iloc[0])\n",
    "\n",
    "bp = axes[1].boxplot(cluster_data_for_plot, labels=cluster_labels_for_plot, patch_artist=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Color the boxes\n",
    "for patch, color in zip(bp['boxes'], colors):\n",
    "    patch.set_facecolor(color)\n",
    "    patch.set_alpha(0.7)\n",
    "\n",
    "axes[1].set_ylabel('CO2 Emission (kg/kWh)', fontsize=11)\n",
    "axes[1].set_title('CO2 Emission Distribution per Cluster', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\n",
    "axes[1].grid(True, alpha=0.3, axis='y')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig('./output/03_Clustering_Results.png', dpi=300, bbox_inches='tight')\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✅ Clustering visualization saved\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 12. CORRELATION HEATMAP"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Correlation analysis\n",
    "correlation_features = ['co2_emission', 'energy_consumption', 'renewable_share', \n",
